{{italic title}}
The '''''Atles dels Ocells Nidificants de Catalunya''''' (Catalan Breeding Bird Atlas) is a critically acclaimed [[Catalan language|Catalan]] [[ornithology|ornithological]] [[atlas]], published in 2004 by the [[Catalan Ornithological Institute]] (ICO) and [[Lynx Edicions]], and edited by Joan Estrada, Vittorio Pedrocchi, Lluis Brotons and Sergi Herrando.  The book presents the results of three years of fieldwork surveying [[Catalonia]]'s breeding [[bird]]s between 1999 and 2002<ref>[http://www.ctfc.cat/docs/bio_document_15.pdf The Catalan Breeding Bird Atlas 1999-2002<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100404002451/http://www.ctfc.cat/docs/bio_document_15.pdf |date=2010-04-04 }}</ref> and consists of 638 pages with maps, graphs, population estimates and trends, with illustrations by [[Toni Llobet]].  Each species has a full account in Catalan with a summary in English.<ref>[http://www.ornitologia.org/monitoratge/atles12.htm Monitoratge - Atles dels Ocells Nidificants de Catalunya<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080510150953/http://www.ornitologia.org/monitoratge/atles12.htm |date=2008-05-10 }}</ref>

